The taxi industry says it did not benefit from the more than R 4 billion the government has spent so far on the taxi recapitalisation programme. Plans to change the taxi industry and save it from the challenges it faces are to be made public by the government during a National Taxi Lekgotla (NTL) which is scheduled for October. Today, the Transport Minister is launching the National Taxi Lekgotla Public Discourse Platform in Germiston, Gauteng. The video below is the live stream of the launch: 